<h1><span id="Nimzowitsch_Defence">Nimzowitsch Defence</span></h1>
<p>Black now faces a strong gambit that if accepted allows white to gain time by attacking the queen's knight.  There are several options for black:
</p>
<dl><dd>3... dxe4 accepts the gambit.  White should play d5 to attack the knight.</dd>
<dd>3... e6 transposes into an inferior variation of the French Defence with the knight blocking the c-pawn.</dd>
<dd>3... a6 an interesting way to decline the gambit as it ignores the attack on d5.</dd></dl>
<p>'1. e4 Nc6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3'
</p>
